            <tr>
              <td class="events">
                <h3><a class="anchor" id="top" name="sandhist"></a>Sanderstead Local History Group. Monthly on a Wednesday</h3>
                <p>Want to discover more local history? If so then 'The Sanderstead Local History Group' would like to invite you to our monthly meetings held 2-4pm at All Saints Church Hall, Onslow Gardens, Sanderstead on the last Wednesday in the month. A small charge of £2 each meeting to cover hall hire and refreshments. No annual fee. Information is on our web site with a link to the Bourne Society where you can find local history books they have produced.</p>
                <p>For 2021 our meetings have been via Zoom and forthcoming meetings are:</p>
                <ul>
                  <li>29th September: Selsdon AD 871 to 1800: A "Country Estate", by Joyce Hoad</li>
                  <li>27th October: Selsdon Park Hotel 1800 - 2000: From country mansion to a magnificent hotel, by Joyce Hoad</li>
                  <li>24th November: All members: An early Christmas party    Decision later whether Zoom or face to face</li>
                </ul>
                <p>Contact Joyce Hoad (Chair) or Chris Harman at sanderssteadlhg@gmail.com if you’d like to be added to our mailing list for Zoom links.</p>               
                </td>
                <td class="events">
